00:44:30.530 --> 00:44:33.200
Is about what do you
sacrifice when you try

00:44:33.200 --> 00:44:35.960
to make this way for assimilation?

00:44:35.960 --> 00:44:40.330
And you know, America likes to
constantly talk about ourselves,

00:44:40.330 --> 00:44:44.010
but we are a really interesting
and fascinating nation that we made

00:44:44.010 --> 00:44:45.700
up of people from all over.

00:44:45.700 --> 00:44:50.070
And that is the tension in
question built into our very fiber

00:44:50.070 --> 00:44:51.610
of our being of this country.

00:44:51.610 --> 00:44:53.970
And I mean, we fight
about it constantly.

00:44:53.970 --> 00:44:59.040
I mean it's at the heart of
probably every kind of major issue

00:44:59.040 --> 00:45:01.290
that we talk about, is
what do you kind of give

00:45:01.290 --> 00:45:03.100
up to become a part of the whole?

00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:06.270
And what are the benefits of
being a part of the whole?

00:45:06.270 --> 00:45:10.030
And can we mourn and can we
acknowledge the things that we lose

00:45:10.030 --> 00:45:13.860
when we try to kind of
become a part of a whole?

00:45:13.860 --> 00:45:16.740 position:56%
And so, those are -- I don't think
those questions are easily answered.

00:45:16.740 --> 00:45:19.340
I mean, I don't think
anybody has a one sentence

00:45:19.340 --> 00:45:21.930
or a three sentence
answer to those questions,

00:45:21.930 --> 00:45:24.320
but I do think they're really
interesting to keep asking

00:45:24.320 --> 00:45:27.440
about these processes that we
do because on the one hand,

00:45:27.440 --> 00:45:31.840
there is the practical need for
a group to assimilate for you

00:45:31.840 --> 00:45:35.890
to be able to work together in some
kind of way, but on the other hand,

00:45:35.890 --> 00:45:39.790
there is so much lost
and there's so much given

00:45:39.790 --> 00:45:42.830
up by the group being asked to
assimilate that is not asked

00:45:42.830 --> 00:45:45.650
of the group that they're
supposed to be assimilating into.

00:45:45.650 --> 00:45:50.990
And so, I think that
tension, for actually I think

00:45:50.990 --> 00:45:56.240 position:56%
where what I find really interesting
about it is when people try to deny

00:45:56.240 --> 00:45:58.910
that that tension exists
for certain things and say

00:45:58.910 --> 00:46:01.100
that it's either all one
way or all the other.

00:46:01.100 --> 00:46:03.410
I don't think it's ever either
all one way or all the other

00:46:03.410 --> 00:46:05.610
for that question around
assimilation.

00:46:05.610 --> 00:46:08.700
I think that tension
is kind of constant.

00:46:08.700 --> 00:46:12.280 position:56%
And people can come up with
different answers and different ways

00:46:12.280 --> 00:46:13.810
of how they're going
to try and figure out.

00:46:13.810 --> 00:46:18.470
And I think each generation of
people comes up with their own way

00:46:18.470 --> 00:46:20.910
of explaining what that's
supposed to be for themselves.

00:46:20.910 --> 00:46:23.850
And a lot of that also comes
from looking at the past,

00:46:23.850 --> 00:46:28.270 position:56%
looking at parents and grandparents,
and what they've had to sacrifice

00:46:28.270 --> 00:46:31.910
or give up, and as a descendent
saying, "Was it really worth it?"

